dct_description_sm: 3 bar scales on map, given in "Cleyne Hollandsse Mylen," "Middelbaer Mylen," and "Groote Mylen."
Oriented with north to the left of sheet.
Creator name taken from initials on map: C.D.H.
Title in banner in middle of map; subtitle in cartouche.
Historical note to the right of title cartouche: Hae ruinae veteris Castri Britanici visae sunt extare, @ 1520, 1552, 1562.
Decorative border and cartouches, elaborate coat of arms and compass rose, buildings and ships.
Dedication and historical note in Latin.
